The paper deals with machine learning techniques for embedding complex data (graphs) into lower dimensional manifolds, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on detecting changes and anomalies in sequences of attributed graphs, which is a problem related to data mining (cs.DM) and anomaly detection (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of conventional methods for numerical streams, which suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions experimental results related to change detection, which could be related to computer vision (cs.CV) if the graphs represent images or visual data.
